Subject: Hodge Deep Research Cycle Realization 001

Description: Bounded deep research pass on mechanisms that produce algebraic cycles from Hodge classes in known or special Hodge cases.

& [ResearchBoundary] is the bounded deep research frame
  + [problem] is Hodge Conjecture
  + [research_gate] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\research\Deep_Research_Priority_Gate.sop
  + [variant_map] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\proof_inquiry\2026-06-26_hodge_variant_boundary_map_001.sop
  + [low_resolution_signal] is cycle-realization mechanisms
  + [bounded_question] is what kinds of mechanisms produce algebraic cycles from Hodge classes in known cases, and whether any resemble the source document's anchor/traversal language

& [SourceSet] is research evidence
  + [source_001] is Clay Mathematics Institute Hodge problem statement
    = url: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hodge.pdf
    = evidence: Hodge classes are conjectured to be rational combinations of algebraic cycle classes, and substitute notions such as absolute Hodge and motivated cycles exist for abelian varieties
  + [source_002] is Arapura and Kang "Known cases of the Hodge conjecture"
    = url: https://arxiv.org/pdf/2105.04695
    = evidence: known cases include divisors via Lefschetz (1,1), cases built from known varieties, and specialized approaches such as Griffiths-Green
  + [source_003] is Voisin "The Hodge conjecture"
    = url: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~claire.voisin/Articlesweb/voisinhodge.pdf
    = evidence: Hodge theory links topological/cohomological invariants and algebraic cycles, but constructing cycles remains the core difficulty
  + [source_004] is Milne "Hodge classes on abelian varieties"
    = url: https://www.jmilne.org/math/Documents/Deligne82.pdf
    = evidence: for abelian varieties, many Hodge classes have strong substitute properties such as absolute or motivated status, but algebraicity remains delicate
  + [source_005] is Green-Griffiths Hodge-theoretic invariants for algebraic cycles
    = url: https://publications.ias.edu/sites/default/files/Hodget.pdf
    = evidence: Hodge-theoretic invariants and filtrations can organize algebraic cycles, but often depend on broader conjectural frameworks

& [Finding] is the mechanism boundary
  + [mechanism_001_known_divisor_realization] is Lefschetz (1,1) turns codimension-one Hodge classes into divisor/algebraic classes
  + [mechanism_002_special_variety_construction] is known cases use special geometry, products, abelian-variety structures, or reductions to already-known cases
  + [mechanism_003_normal_function_variation] is variation/normal-function approaches can detect or organize cycles in families
  + [mechanism_004_motivated_or_absolute_substitute] is absolute Hodge or motivated cycles imitate algebraic-cycle behavior but do not automatically prove algebraicity
  + [mechanism_005_explicit_cycle_search] is explicit construction on hypersurfaces or special families can produce candidates, but not a general method
  + [open_shape] is no general traversal from arbitrary rational Hodge class to algebraic cycle is known

& [SymbolicResolution] is the updated concept shape
  + [memory_anchor] is candidate rational Hodge class only after formal scoping
  + [walk_the_space] maps_to cycle construction or variation-in-family method, not mere conceptual traversal
  + [phase_stability] maps_to Hodge type/rationality recognition, not realization
  + [algebraic_behavior] requires actual cycle class map image

& [NextToolNeed] is the emergent tool shape
  + [tool_needed] is yes
  + [tool_name] is Hodge Cycle Realization Mechanism Table
  + [tool_purpose] is compare realization mechanisms by scope, construction strength, known-case status, and relation to memory-anchor/traversal language

& [Disposition] is the pass result
  + [decision] is continue_with_cycle_realization_mechanism_table
  + [heartbeat_status] is active every minute

& [ToolResolution] is the next heartbeat work result
  + [tool] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\seven_math_problems\proof_inquiry\Hodge_Cycle_Realization_Mechanism_Table.sop
  + [table_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\proof_inquiry\2026-06-26_hodge_cycle_realization_mechanism_table_001.sop
  + [table_finding] is traversal-like methods organize or search, but Hodge proof needs scoped algebraic cycle output
  + [recommended_next] is project Git reflection before moving to P vs NP
